consolidated loss and loss adjustment expense ratio of 72.9% in 2011 was 11.9 points higher than the loss and loss adjustment expense ratio of 61.0% in 2010. catastrophe losses
accounted for 11.6 points and 5.2 points of the 2011 and 2010 loss and loss adjustment expense ratios, respectively. net favorable prior year reserve development provided 3.2 points and 5.8 points of
benefit to the consolidated loss and loss adjustment expense ratio in 2011 and 2010, respectively. the consolidated loss and loss adjustment expense ratio excluding catastrophe losses and prior year
reserve development in 2011 was 2.9 points higher than the 2010 ratio on the same basis, primarily reflecting the impact of loss cost trends and higher non-catastrophe weather-related
losses.
